  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6575 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6560 and positive gamma wall at 6600, dealers are currently in forced buying mode as they hedge short gamma positions during this fresh regime flip to BREAKOUT. The massive -43.5B total GEX and concentrated negative gamma between 6550-6570 means dealers will aggressively buy any dip toward 6560 and below, while the 6600 positive gamma wall will trigger dealer selling pressure on any push higher. Watch 6560 as the critical amplifying level where dealer buying accelerates, and 6600 as the key resistance where dealer selling kicks in to cap upside.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile whipsaw action between 6560 and 6600 with dealers amplifying moves in both directions.",
